Date of Birth: June 18, 1879<br/>
Birthplace: Mendon, Utah, USA<br/>
Ordained apostle: January 18, 1917<br/>
Death: May 19, 1959<br/>
<br/>
Born June 18, 1879, at Mendon, Cache Co., Utah, to Stephen Longstroth Richards and Emma Louise Stayner. Ordained apostle Jan. 18, 1917, by Joseph R Smith, at age 37;
sustained as first counselor to President David 0. McKay April 9, 1951, at age 71;
died May 19, 1959, at Salt Lake City, Salt Lake Co., Utah, at age 79.